> Hi, I have checke the latest code,
> 
> AbstractServiceConfig#getListener() has been changed to:
> 
> ```java
>     @Parameter(key = Constants.EXPORTER_LISTENER_KEY, append = true)
>     public String getListener() {
>         return this.listener;
>     }
> 
>     @Override
>     public void setListener(String listener) {
>         checkMultiExtension(ExporterListener.class, "listener", listener);
>         super.setListener(listener);
>     }
> ```
> 
> So this is not an issue anymore.
你确定么?现在是2019年了 master版本和你说的不一样啊. 还有别人用中文问问题,你为什么用英文回答呢??

> ```
>    String ip = invoker.getUrl().getIp();
>     int port = invoker.getUrl().getPort();
>     String message ="ls -l "+invoker.getUrl().getServiceInterface();
>     String paramsStr = Telnet.getInstance().sendCommand(ip,port,message,"dubbo>");
>     paramsStr = StringUtils.substringBetween(paramsStr,"(",")");
>     return paramsStr.split(",");
> ```
> 
> ```
> public class Telnet {
>     private Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(Telnet.class);
> 
>     private static Telnet telnet = new Telnet();
> 
>     public static Telnet getInstance() {
>         return telnet;
>     }
> 
>     public String sendCommand(String ip, int port, String message, String suffix){
>         TelnetClient telnet = new TelnetClient();
>         try {
>             telnet.connect(ip,port);
>             InputStream in = telnet.getInputStream();
>             PrintStream out =new PrintStream(telnet.getOutputStream());
>             out.println(message);
>             out.flush();
>             StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer();
>             char ch = (char) in.read();
>             while (true) {
>                 sb.append(ch);
>                 if (ch == '>') {
>                     if (sb.toString().endsWith(suffix)) {
>                         break;
>                     }
>                 }
>                 ch = (char) in.read();
>             }
>             return sb.toString();
>         } catch (IOException e) {
>             logger.error(e.getMessage(),e);
>         }finally {
>             try {
>                 telnet.disconnect();
>             } catch (IOException e) {
>             }
>         }
>         return null;
>     }
> }
> ```

我已经解决了, Actor 异步版本 [https://github.com/asura-pro/indigo-api/tree/master/asura-dubbo/src/main/scala/asura/dubbo/actor](https://github.com/asura-pro/indigo-api/tree/master/asura-dubbo/src/main/scala/asura/dubbo/actor)

> 服务端接不到是因为TagContextFilter中的invoke方法进行了attachments.remove(TOKEN_KEY);
> 不使用“token”以及其他KEY不被remove调就可以了

哈哈，这其实也是dubbo的锅，理论上暴露给用户直接使用的方法，dubbo都应该尽量避免key和用户的key冲突，比如dubbo内部应该使用_dubbo_token这类不容易和用户冲突的key

一个不完美的解决方法是：
```java
@Autowired
@Lazy
F6HttpInterface f6HttpInterface;
```
